docs.abstract: It was not clear how the presidential pardon would help the late boxing champion, whose conviction for refusing the military draft was overturned in 1971.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump said on Friday that he is considering pardoning Muhammad Ali, a boxing legend who died two years ago and was convicted of refusing to be drafted during the Vietnam War. But it was not immediately clear what Mr. Trump sought to pardon, as Mr. Ali’s conviction was overturned nearly 50 years ago.

headline.main: Trump Says He’s Considering a Pardon for Muhammad Ali
headline.print_headline: Trump Jabs at a Pardon, But Ali Is Beyond Reach
